  ('Open Philanthropy Project','Center for Applied Rationality',1035000,'2016-07-01','month','donation log','Rationality improvement/effective altruism/movement growth','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/giving/grants/center-applied-rationality-general-support','Grant over two years. Usage split: 915000 will support workshops and organizational improvements, and 120000 will fund a pilot version of EuroSPARC, an eight-day summer program in Europe run by CFAR for mathematically gifted high school students, modeled on SPARC (see also https://www.openphilanthropy.org/giving/grants/center-applied-rationality-sparc the separate grant to SPARC). Reasons for grants include value alignment, improving rationality, highlighting risks for advanced AI and other GCRs, successful pipeline-building to things like the effective altruism movement',NULL,'United States|Europe',NULL,NULL, '2016-09-06', 'day', 'https://groups.google.com/a/openphilanthropy.org/forum/#!topic/newly.published/XkSl27jBDZ8',NULL),
